                <td width="436" class="texte"> 
                  <table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0">
                  <tr><td><span class="text-titre">Banexi Ventures</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="texte">Banexi Ventures II and III are funds managed by Banexi Ventures Partners (BNP Paribas Group), one of the leading French Venture Capital firms. Since 1983, Banexi Ventures Partners provides early stage financing to high tech companies in targeted sectors: biotechnology, microelectronics, optics, semiconductor and information technology. It has unique expertise in this sector, with more than 200 investments in fast growing start-ups</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="HTTP://www.banexiventures.com" class="texte">www.banexiventures.com</a></td></tr>                  </table>
<BR>
                  <table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0">
                  <tr><td><span class="text-titre">ParTech International</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="texte">ParTech International is a venture capital firm that provides financing for start-up and emerging growth companies in Europe, United States and Asia. Located in Paris, San Francisco and Tokyo, ParTech manages in excess of $ 800 million drawn from a broad base of world-class institutions as IBM, Bell Atlantic, GTE Pension Funds, insurance companies like AXA, AGF, Liverpool Victoria and Bank Vontobel. Since the 80's ParTech's unified team has been managing with success a global portfolio specialized in Information Technology as Fluxus, Swan, Vignette, Informatica, Softway International, Business Objects, BreezeCom, Digital Island, Protégé, TravelPrice, and Mediapps.</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="HTTP://www.partechintl.com" class="texte">www.partechintl.com</a></td></tr>                  </table>
<BR>
                  <table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0">
                  <tr><td><span class="text-titre">Viventures</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="texte">Viventures, a venture capital fund present in the United States (San Francisco, CA), Europe (Paris) and Asia (Singapore), provides venture funding as well as strategic and financial guidance to promising information technology and telecommunication start-ups. The first Viventures fund was launched in September 1998 by Vivendi Universal. At December 31, 2000, the fund had raised US $112.2 million and invested in 49 companies with 18 leading financial and industrial corporations. Viventures second fund, Viventures 2, announced in January 2001, was capitalized at 635 million euros (US $ 598.5 million) as at April 2000. The presence of over 30 corporate and financial investors from Europe, the U.S., Asia and India confirms the fund¹s global character and reinforces the long-term financial objectives of the fund¹s portfolio companies and their investors. Viventures 2 has been available since June 2000 and has already invested in eleven companies in Europe, the U.S. and Asia.</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="HTTP://www.viventures.com" class="texte">www.viventures.com</a></td></tr>                  </table>
